But that demonstrative power which is inherent in the particle was particularly em- ployed by ancient usage in such a manner, that by it the speaker marked with a certain affirmative force those things ¹ which he avowed concerning himself and his own opinion, or in regard to his own affairs. Hence it happened that equidem was joined, as a general rule, with the first person of the verb.
